 Port Elizabeth - The Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service says notable rains were recorded in Port Elizabeth, George, East London and Plettenberg Bay on Wednesday night. "We experienced some nice rain showers overnight, which were mainly confined to the coast," said Garth Sampson, the SA Weather Service's Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape. He described that notable figures were: "Over the interior to the east there were some good falls in places, with Fort Beaufort recording 10mm and Bisho 11mm," Sampson said. "We can expect some more light showers this morning along the coast and adjacent interior, east of Cape St Francis. "Conditions will clear for the weekend." Station Names 10 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 10.0 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 8.4 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 8.4 ARS Chatty 11.6 AWS Coega 1.0 AWSH Fettes Road 5.8 ARS Flower Reserve 11.0 AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 8.0 ARS St Albans 6.6 AWS Uitenhage 0.6 Man Woodridge 7.4 Catchment  AWS Joubertina 1.4 ARS Kareedouw 4.2 Man Kareedouw 6.5 Man Kouga Dam 0.0 AWS Patensie 2.2    Other Towns  AWS Addo 2.2 AWS Bisho/KWT 11.4 AWS Cape St Francis 4.0 AWS Cradock NIL AWS East London 14.6 AWS Fort Beaufort 9.6 AWS George 10.4 AWS Graaff Reinet NIL AWS Grahamstown 2.4 AWS Henry`s Flats 0.4 AWS Joubertina 1.4 AWS Mossel Bay 4.0 AWS Mthatha 9.4 AWS Plettenberg bay 20.0 AWS Port Alfred 4.4 AWS Queenstown NIL  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  